cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

This paper is primarily focused on object recognition using a neural network architecture inspired by predictive coding theory in neuroscience. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of local recurrent processing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the training and testing of the neural network, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of predictive coding theory also falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the convergence of internal representations over time, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
